<common-name datatype='string'>atpBEFHAGDC</common-name>
<comment datatype='string'>FNR represses &lt;i&gt;atpB&lt;/i&gt; gene expression under anaerobiosis [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12754220&quot;&gt;Salmon03&lt;/a&gt;]. Under nitrogen-rich growth conditions, the expression of the &lt;i&gt;atpA&lt;/i&gt; gene increased in a mutant for the transcriptional regulator Fnr. However, under nitrogen-limited growth conditions, the gene expression was decreased.  Under both nitrogen-limited and nitrogen-rich growth conditions, the expression of &lt;i&gt;atpA&lt;/i&gt; increased  in the mutants for &lt;i&gt;cyoA&lt;/i&gt; and Fur. However, it is unknown if the effects of the transcriptional regulators act directly on the gene expression; also, it is unknown which of the three promoters that transcribe the gene could  be regulated by the regulators [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21272324&quot;&gt;Kumar11&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;
The &lt;i&gt;atpB&lt;/i&gt; mRNA is the most unstable region within the &lt;i&gt;atp&lt;/i&gt; operon, mainly in the residues 93-171.  This instability causes a toxic phenotype in the cell [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12860393&quot;&gt;Arechaga03&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;i&gt;atpB&lt;/i&gt; is upregulated and downregulated in response to chlortetracycline (CTC) and nalidixic acid (NA), respectively, in parallel and in the opposite direction with &lt;i&gt;ompC&lt;/i&gt; gene [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22960566&quot;&gt;Lin12&lt;/a&gt;]; these changes are regulated by CpxR [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22960566&quot;&gt;Lin12&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;
The expression of the gene &lt;i&gt;atpA&lt;/i&gt; is increased under acidic growth conditions in either aerobiosis or microaerobiosis [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23274360&quot;&gt;Marzan13&lt;/a&gt;].</comment>
